            "body": "> Makes perfect sense, given that before it was using `make_position_params` and there is no reason AFAICT not to make that parameterized.\r\n\r\nYes, besides, I believe `vim.pos` will help us reduce the number of functions in `vim.lsp.util`, which is quite a messy module. For example, it currently has two versions of `make_position_param`: one for creating `lsp.Position` and another for creating `lsp.TextDocumentPositionParams`.\r\n\r\n",
